'Yajna,' brother Yudhishthir.

98
00:17:21,920 --> 00:17:22,920
Yes, Nakul.

99
00:17:23,880 --> 00:17:25,760
I will go to Hastinapur soon

100
00:17:25,850 --> 00:17:27,920
and seek grandsire's permission
for the Rajsuya 'Yajna.'

101
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:31,750
Pardon me,
brother Yudhishthir

102
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:34,690
but

103
00:17:34,850 --> 00:17:37,830
independence can never be had
through someone's permission.

104
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:41,850
It is procured through
one's resolution.

105
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,660
The entire Aryan region

106
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,890
is afflicted
with unrighteousness.

107
00:17:49,820 --> 00:17:52,630
The basis of a kingdom
is the happiness of the subjects

108
00:17:53,750 --> 00:17:55,700
and not the prosperity
of the King

109
00:17:57,620 --> 00:18:05,660
but majority of the Kings
are forgetting this key fact.

110
00:18:02,720 --> 00:18:05,660
The task of making them
adhere to righteousness

111
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:08,640
can be done only by you,
King Yudhishthir.

112
00:18:09,750 --> 00:18:12,630
We must conduct
the Rajsuya 'Yajna' soon.

113
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:16,660
We must make those Kings
adhere to righteousness

114
00:18:18,620 --> 00:18:20,620
and the ones who refuse
to adhere to it

115
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,660
must be annihilated

116
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:27,890
otherwise there will
come a time, Your Highness

117
00:18:28,820 --> 00:18:31,690
when, despite wanting
to adhere to righteousness

118
00:18:32,820 --> 00:18:35,590
one will be unable to do so.

119
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:38,750
Everyone will

120
00:18:40,620 --> 00:18:42,690
take to the path
of unrighteousness.

121
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,600
Vrushali.

122
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:56,510
It was a question of the
Crown Prince's future, Vrushali.

123
00:20:00,530 --> 00:20:02,530
Had I not accepted
this position again

124
00:20:03,730 --> 00:20:05,540
forming an alliance
with Emperor Jarasandha

125
00:20:05,570 --> 00:20:06,600
would have been impossible

126
00:20:07,770 --> 00:20:09,610
and a crucial plan

127
00:20:11,530 --> 00:20:12,530
would also have fallen through.

128
00:20:15,800 --> 00:20:17,750
That is why, the Crown Prince
requested... - A plan?

129
00:20:21,600 --> 00:20:22,770
Was the plan successful,
Radheya?

130
00:20:26,530 --> 00:20:27,640
No, Vrushali.

131
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:30,640
Situations have changed now

132
00:20:32,530 --> 00:20:34,570
but the moment I had decided
to become King again

133
00:20:36,630 --> 00:20:38,700
