134
00:20:39,700 --> 00:20:41,580
which was,
in order to help my friend

135
00:20:41,600 --> 00:20:42,740
to be prepared to make

136
00:20:44,730 --> 00:20:46,610
any sacrifice asked of me.

137
00:20:48,630 --> 00:20:50,510
Is there any circumstance

138
00:20:51,470 --> 00:20:52,670
that never changes?

139
00:20:58,700 --> 00:21:00,650
During the darkness
of a solar eclipse

140
00:21:02,530 --> 00:21:04,710
birds return to their nests

141
00:21:07,570 --> 00:21:09,550
not because it is night

142
00:21:12,500 --> 00:21:13,600
but because

143
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,510
they deem the day to be so

144
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:20,670
but night-time
follows eventually.

145
00:21:25,570 --> 00:21:27,480
Bearing a crown on the head

146
00:21:28,670 --> 00:21:30,670
does not bring about a change
in one's heart, Vrushali.

147
00:21:37,430 --> 00:21:38,470
I am still the same.

148
00:21:40,430 --> 00:21:42,470
This crown is my duty, Vrushali.

149
00:21:45,630 --> 00:21:47,670
That is why, I am compelled
to bear its burden.

150
00:21:59,570 --> 00:22:02,440
But I assure you,
Vrushali

151
00:22:03,500 --> 00:22:04,670
that I will

152
00:22:05,570 --> 00:22:07,510
never commit an incorrect deed.

153
00:22:10,430 --> 00:22:11,540
Is your

154
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:13,470
will power your own, Radheya?

155
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:16,380
If you had that independence

156
00:22:17,530 --> 00:22:19,440
then why would you have to
bear that crown again?

